The bus was carrying about 55 passengers when the driver apparently lost control on the Hemel-en-Aarde road on Thursday afternoon. CAPE TOWN - Eight people are in hospital after a bus crash in Caledon, in the Western Cape. The bus was carrying about 55 passengers when the driver apparently lost control on the Hemel-en-Aarde road on Thursday afternoon. Provincial traffic chief Kenny Africa says the bus driver says the brakes had failed. “We’re taking the bus to the testing station for a roadworthy test and the driver has also been charged with reckless and negligent driving.”